## Running Code

To run code from a php file, execute: `bin/run <filename>`
(If there is an error about permissions, run `chmod +x bin/run` and try again)

Example: bin/run src/foo.php

## Running Tests

To run the unit tests, execute: `bin/tests`. This will execute all unit tests, configured in the config file (phpunit.xml)
If you want to run a singe test case just append the filename to the command.

Example: `bin/tests tests/FizzBuzzTest.php`

You can pass every parameter to `bin/tests` which you can pass to phpunit
